oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Wyrick funeral
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Fenders Methodist Church Cemetery showing the funeral of Mrs. Amanda Jayne Mahon Wyrick (1852-1936) of the Luttrell community. All nine of her children are gathered around her grave: Sarah, William, Laura, Nancy, Arzelo, Jonas, Susie, Minnie and E. Lenore. Writing at the top and bottom of the negative reads: "Fender / [Wyrick] Children at Mother's Grave. July 2."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Funeral rites & ceremonies; Families
